he abased Christ, but to follow after him. The Abased Christ aims to enrich historical theologians’ appreciation of Kierkegaard’s Christology. However, it concludes by grappling with questions of power, agency, and sacrifice which have been at the forefront of contemporary theology in the 20th and 21st centuries, thereby suggesting how we might make sense of Kierkegaard’s Christology today.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aChristologie. 4aGeschichtsphilosophie. 4aKierkegaard, Søren. 4aTheologie.  aChristology.  aKierkegaard.  aphilosophy of history.  atheology.0 cEPUBz97831109895190 cprintz978311099971640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311098946540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110989465423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110989465/original  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK